resources.name: show
store
update
resources.description:
Use this endpoint to edit a user. Enter the user ID in the URL. You need to pass the access token in the header of this request. Parameters: 
[user_id] = required | integer
[email] = string
[name] = string
[password] = string | min 8 char, 1 number, 1 upper char
[date_of_birth] = string | format Y-m-d
CURL example: 
curl --request PUT \
  --url http:///api/users/1 \
  --header 'Accept: application/json' \
  --header 'Authorization: Bearer $access_token' \
  --header 'Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded' \
  --data email=example@example.com \
  --data 'name=Example Name' \
  --data password=SomePassword01 \
  --data date_of_birth=1985-03-15
Example of successful return: 
{
  "error": false,
  "message": "User edited successfully!",
  "data": {
    "user": {
      "id": 16,
      "email": "example@example.com",
      "name": "Example Name",
      "date_of_birth": "1985-03-15",
      "active": true
    }
  }
}
Example of return with error. Validation errors contain the name of the field and the message: 
{
  "error": true,
  "message": "Error editing the User!",
  "data": {
    "validations": {
      "email": "Email already exists!"
    }
  }
}

resources.name: delete
resources.description:
Use this endpoint to delete the user. Enter the user ID in the URL. You need to pass the access token in the header of this request. Parameters: 
[user_id] = required | integer
CURL Example: 
curl --request DELETE \
  --url http:///api/users/1 \
  --header 'Accept: application/json' \
  --header 'Authorization: Bearer $access_token' \
  --header 'Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded'
Example of successful return: 
{
  "error": false,
  "message": "User successfully deleted!"
}
Example of return with error: 
{
  "error": true,
  "message": "Can't delete other user register."
}

resources.name: activate
resources.description:
Use this endpoint to activate/deactivate a user. Enter the user ID and the activate/deactivate parameter in the URL. You need to pass the access token in the header of this request. Parameters: 
[user_id] = required | integer
[activate_or_deactivate] = required | integer (0 = deactivate, 1 = activate)
CURL example: 
curl --request PATCH \
  --url http:///api/users/1/0 \
  --header 'Accept: application/json' \
  --header 'Authorization: Bearer $access_token' \
  --header 'Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded'
Example of successful return: 
{
  "error": false,
  "message": "User edited successfully! Action: activated",
  "data": {
    "user": {
      "id": 16,
      "email": "example@example.com",
      "name": "Example Name",
      "date_of_birth": "1985-03-15",
      "active": true
    }
  }
}
Example of return with error. Validation errors contain the name of the field and the message: 
{
  "error": true,
  "message": "Can't change other user register."
}

resources.name: show
store
update
activate
resources.description:
Use this endpoint to activate/deactivate a book. Enter the book ID and the activate/deactivate parameter in the URL. You need to pass the access token in the header of this request. Parameters: 
[book id] = required | integer
[activate_or_deactivate] = required | integer (0 = deactivate, 1 = activate)
CURL example: 
curl --request PATCH \
  --url /api/books/1/1 \
  --header 'Accept: application/json' \
  --header 'Authorization: Bearer $access_token' \
  --header 'Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded'
Example of successful return: 
{
  "error": false,
  "message": "Book edited successfully! Action: activated",
  "data": {
    "book": {
      "id": 1,
      "title": "Dolores error numquam quam omnis.",
      "isbn": "1564161447",
      "published_at": "2018-01-02",
      "status": "AVAILABLE",
      "active": true
    }
  }
}
Example of return with error. Validation errors contain the name of the field and the message: 
{
  "error": true,
  "message": "Book #40 not found!"
}

resources.name: checkout
resources.description:
Use this endpoint to check out a book for the logged in user - get the book from the library. Enter the book ID parameter in the URL. You need to pass the access token in the header of this request. Parameters: 
[book_id] = required | integer
CURL example: 
curl --request POST \
  --url /api/books/checkout/1 \
  --header 'Accept: application/json' \
  --header 'Authorization: Bearer $access_token' \
  --header 'Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded'
Example of successful return: 
{
  "error": false,
  "message": "Check-out book successfully!"
}
Example of return with error. 
{
  "error": true,
  "message": "Book #2 is unavailable!"
}

resources.name: checkin
resources.description:
Use this endpoint to check in a book - returns the book to the library. Enter the book ID parameter in the URL. You need to pass the access token in the header of this request. Parameters: 
[book_id] = required | integer
CURL example: 
curl --request POST \
  --url /api/books/checkin/1 \
  --header 'Accept: application/json' \
  --header 'Authorization: Bearer $access_token' \
  --header 'Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded'
Example of successful return: 
{
  "error": false,
  "message": "Check-in book successfully!"
}
Example of return with error. 
{
  "error": true,
  "message": "Can not check-in an available Book #2!"
}

resources.name: Login
resources.description:
Use this endpoint to login. Save the access token to be able to perform other operations. The access token is valid for one hour. Parameters: 
[email] = required | string
[password] = required | string
CURL example: 
curl --request POST \
  --url /api/login \
  --header 'Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded' \
  --data email=example@example.com \
  --data password=SomePassword01

}
